Postdoctoral Fellows

Chandler Goldman

Dr. Chandler Goldman received a PhD in 2020 at the Medical College of Georgia at Augusta University, where he worked with Dr. Graydon Gonsalvez to elucidate mechanisms that control cell fate decisions. He joined the Lewis Lab in the Fall of 2020.

Former Members

Abigail Ameri -

Abigail Ameri received her B.S in Bioinformatics from Ramapo College of New Jersey, where she investigated salt tolerance in Spartina alterniflora. She joined the graduate program at UGA in 2015, and was awarded an NSF Graduate Research Fellowship in 2016. She received her PhD in the Lewis lab in 2020 (Lab Publications).

Aileen Ferraro -
Former graduate student Aileen Ferraro received a BS in Biology from Southern Connecticut State University in 2014. From 2014 to 2015, she was a Postgraduate Associate in the department of Microbial Pathogenesis at Yale Medicine, where she studied the role of the Type III secretion system and effector proteins in Shigella flexneri pathogenesis. She joined the UGA graduate program in 2015 and was awarded an NSF Graduate Research Fellowship in 2015. Dr. Ferraro received her PhD in the Lewis Lab in 2020 (Lab Publications). After working as a postdoctoral fellow at the University of Minnesota, she accepted a position with Azenta Life Sciences.

Masayuki Kamei -
Dr. Kamei is a Japan Society of Promotion for Sciences Research Fellow (2013). He received his B.S. and his PhD from the School of Life Sciences at Toyo University in Japan, where he worked with the model fungus Neurospora crassa to investigate the effects and cellular responses to antifungal drugs. In 2013, he received fellowship from  the Japan Society of Promotion for Sciences (DC2&PD). He joined the Lewis lab as a postdoc in 2014. He made multiple contributions in the lab, including identification of the chromatin remodeler ISWI as a key factor for transcriptional silencing in N. crassa (Kamei Contributions). Following his postdoctoral work, Dr. Kamei accepted a position with Abcam.

Yael Bar-Peled

Yael Bar-Peled is a graduate of the University of Georgia. She worked as a technician in the Lewis lab from 2019-2020 (Bar-Peled Contributions). She is current pursuing her graduate degree in Genetic Counseling at the University of Alabama - Birmingham School of Medicine.

Eve Basenko - Dr. Basenko was a postdoc in the Lewis lab from 2012 - 2016 (Basenko Contributions). She accepted a position at the University of Liverpool, where she works as the fungal research community outreach liaison for the fungal genomics database, FungiDB.

Kelsey Lynch - Dr. Kelsey Lynch was a technician in the Lewis Lab in 2011 - 2012 (Lynch Contributions). She went on to receive her PhD from the University of Washington and is currently a postdoc at the Fred Hutchinson Cancer Center.

Cameron Prybol- Cameron Prybol was a technician in the Lewis Lab in 2015. Following the lab, he joined the graduate program and Stanford Medical school and is currently working for a start-up.

Takahiko Sasaki - Dr. Sasaki received his PhD in the Lewis lab in 2015 (Sasaki Contributions).

Michael Seymour - Mike Seymour was an MS student in the lab (Seymour Contributions). He is currently working as a research technician for the US-ARS.

Ashley Hagen - Ashley was an MS student in the lab. She is currently working as a science communications specialist for the American Society for Microbiology.
